item.title: Impossibile to compile any patches (Windows 10)
item.dc:creator: @more_urgent_jest Jurgen
item.description:
@more_urgent_jest wrote:

yes, I tried clicking Reset All in preferences and that deleted all the demo patches, but they weren't downloaded again.

repairing the install didn't work either.

uninstalling and reinstalling did.

I wonder if it happened, because I installed before I unzipped the run time.

Is there a dependency there?

Read full topic

item.title: Impossibile to compile any patches (Windows 10)
item.dc:creator: @thetechnobear Mark Harris
item.description:
@thetechnobear wrote:

looks like either that particular patch is corrupted, or the library download has failed.

try another demo patch,
if that fails, reset the all libraries (make sure you have an internet connection) in preferences
(allowing it to delete the libraries)

Read full topic

item.title: Impossibile to compile any patches (Windows 10)
item.dc:creator: @johannes johannes
item.description:
@johannes wrote:

A quick guess, if this happened suddenly, maybe a virus-scanner decided to quarantine the arm-none-eabi-g++ executable? It should be in C:\Program Files (x86)\axoloti_runtime\platform_win\bin
Could you re-install the axoloti runtime?
